    "result": "ExamManifestMemento",
    "wp_note": "Enumerates the provekit-exam-manifest/v1.1 question set the substrate considers part of canonical coverage at concept_hub_version. The v1.1 wire contract narrows realization to concept-realization per concept and language, embeds tag kind in RealizationMemento, and uses boundary-realization per native target library and boundary contract. The manifest itself is stable and content-addressed; per-question coverage (answered/refused/open) is captured in a separate ExamCoverageMemento family deferred to future work. Loaded by consumers (cluster, bind, lift plugins, federation handshake) to cite specific questions in their outputs (gap records, refusal mementos, plugin registry mementos)."
